articles.author: Steve Holland, Joseph Ax, Bianca Flowers, Jarrett Renshaw
articles.description: Donald Trump was elected U.S. president, capping a remarkable comeback four years after he was voted out of the White House and ushering in a new American leadership likely to test democratic institutions at home and relations abroad.
articles.title: Trump secures White House comeback victory, defeating Harris

articles.author: Sarah Marsh, Andreas Rinke
articles.description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz sacked his Finance Minister Christian Lindner on Wednesday after weeks of wrangling over the economic direction of the government, sources told Reuters.
articles.title: Germany's Scholz sacks his finance minister, leaving govt's future unclear

articles.author: Anastasiia Malenko
articles.description: Ukraine appealed to Donald Trump's image as a tough leader on Wednesday in the hope of persuading the returning U.S. president not to abandon its cause in pursuit of peace with Russia.
articles.title: Facing uncertain fate under Trump, Ukraine appeals to his 'strength'

articles.author: Jason Lange, Bo Erickson, Brad Heath
articles.description: Donald Trump reshaped the U.S. electorate once again this year, piling up support among Hispanic voters, young people, and Americans without college degrees -- and winning more votes in nearly all of the country as he reclaimed the presidency.
articles.title: Trump's return to power fueled by Hispanic, working-class voter support

articles.author: Angelo Amante, John Irish
articles.description: U.N. nuclear watchdog chief Rafael Grossi said on Wednesday he might head to Iran in the coming days to discuss its disputed atomic programme and that he expected to work cooperatively with U.S. President-elect Donald Trump.
articles.title: UN nuclear watchdog chief says he may head to Iran soon as Trump return looms

articles.author: Alasdair Pal
articles.description: Australia Prime Minister Anthony Albanese said on Thursday the government would legislate for a ban on social media for children under 16, a policy the government says is world-leading.
articles.title: Australia proposes ban on social media for those under 16

articles.author: Timothy Gardner
articles.description: Former President Donald Trump's return to the White House could mean tougher enforcement of U.S. oil sanctions against Iran, potentially trimming global supplies, but his administration could struggle to get China, Iran's top crude customer, to cooperate, analysts said.
articles.title: Trump could harden Iran oil stance but struggle to stem flow to China, analysts say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Australia's ambassador in Washington, Kevin Rudd, deleted comments he previously made about Donald Trump after the Republican's election win, saying on Thursday they did not reflect the view of the Australian government.
articles.title: Australia's ambassador in Washington deletes Trump comments after election win

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Plea deals agreed with the man accused of masterminding the Sept. 11 attacks and two accomplices held at the U.S. military prison at Guantanamo Bay, Cuba, were valid, according to a judge's ruling reported by the New York Times on Wednesday regarding agreements that had been revoked by the Pentagon.
articles.title: Judge rules Guantanamo plea deals revoked by Pentagon were valid- New York Times

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Japanese Prime Minister Shigeru Ishiba is trying to arrange a stopover in the United States later this month to meet with U.S. President-elect Donald Trump, four sources with knowledge of the matter said.
articles.title: Japan PM Ishiba seeking meeting with Trump in US this month
